public final class Creative
extends GenericJson

Model definition for Creative.

This is the Java data model class that specifies how to parse/serialize into the JSON that is transmitted over HTTP when working with the Ad Exchange Buyer API. For a detailed explanation see: http://code.google.com/p/google-api-java-client/wiki/Json

Author:
Google, Inc.

getDisapprovalReasons

public List<String> getDisapprovalReasons()
The reason for disapproval, if any. Note that not all disapproval reasons may be categorized, so it is possible for the creative to have a status of DISAPPROVED with an empty list for disapproval_reasons. In this case, please reach out to your TAM to help debug the issue. Read- only. This field should not be set in requests. The value returned may be null.

setResponseHeaders

public void setResponseHeaders(HttpHeaders responseHeaders)
Sets the HTTP headers returned with the server response, or null. This member should only be non-null if this object was the top level element of a response. For example, a request that returns a single Creative would include the response headers, while a request which returns an array of Creative, would have a non-null response header in the enclosing object only.
